<br>
I actually got quite a few CDs from Columbia House and some tapes - once upon a time.  However, I found out how they get you.<br>
<br>
Once I had grown up, I signed up for the Video Club.  The rule was that I got my videos, and I think I had to order 3 more to &quot;pay my dues&quot;.  <br>
<br>
After I bought the three, I continued to get tapes.  They continued to bill my credit card for them.  My credit card was a check card.  So it came out of my bank account.  I didn't really mind much.  I got some good tapes and sent back the ones I didn't want.  However, at some point, they started sending me like 3 tapes a month.  I was supposed to be eligible for a free tape for every &quot;howevermany&quot; tapes I bought.  I never recieved any free tapes.  Ever.  Not after the initial 5 or so I ordered in the beginning.  <br>
<br>
I called repeatedly and asked them to cancel me.  They did not.  They bill you right around the time the tapes arrive.  It's pretty random and not like &quot;once a month at this time&quot;.  During a particularly rough time in my finances, I called and demanded they remove me.  They did not.  They sent 3 more tapes at one time and billed me for them.  What did I get?  I got to pay the overdraft charge to my bank.  I still have the tapes and since my bank said they had no way to block them, I had to close that account and get a new one.  <br>
<br>
So even if you do always pay your dues, you get screwed in the end anyway.  <br>
